A number of users have requested that we provide functionality to let them preset the permissions which a space is given, upon creation. 

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of June 05,  2012|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3C78B5| titleBGColor=#3C78B5| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
Thanks everyone for the helpful feedback and your patience.

This issue is now on our roadmap and we expect it will be implemented by the end of the year.{panel}

The recently updated list for a space doesn't do any processing of its content.  At the very least it should turn < into &lt;

Our confluence source is like this:
-----------begin source-----------------------------
Example:
{code:xml}
<font name="Verdana" size="19"/>
{code}
More examples...
-----------end source-----------------------------


When we view the space summary, the recently updated list shows "More examples" in a huge font, overlapping other layout.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-2549].
  {panel}

Trackbacks only work if the full URL is included in a page's source, bit if the URL is created by a macro. So, for example, If I have a page with a link such as:

    http://jira:8080/browse/BLA-49

then trackbacks work fine, but if I have a link inside a macro, such as:

    {issue:BLA-50}

where the issue macro is defined as:

     <a href="http://jira:8080/browse/$param1">$param1</a>

then a trackback is not created.
